# =============================================================================
# React Weather Application - Environment Variables Template
# =============================================================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to create a new file named '.env' in the project root:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
#
# 3. Never commit your .env file to version control (it should be in .gitignore)
#
# 4. Restart the development server after making changes to .env
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OpenWeatherMap API Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose: Used for fetching current weather data and weather forecasts
# 
# How to obtain:
#   1. Sign up at https://openweathermap.org/api
#   2. Navigate to your API keys section
#   3. Copy your API key and paste it below
#
# Documentation: https://openweathermap.org/api/one-call-api
#
REACT_APP_OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY=your_openweathermap_api_key_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API Ninjas Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose: Used for city search and geolocation services
#
# How to obtain:
#   1. Sign up at https://api-ninjas.com/
#   2. Navigate to your dashboard to find your API key
#   3. Copy your API key and paste it below
#
# Documentation: https://api-ninjas.com/api/city
#
REACT_APP_API_NINJAS_KEY=your_api_ninjas_key_here

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTICE
# =============================================================================
#
# ⚠️  CLIENT-SIDE EXPOSURE WARNING:
#
# Environment variables prefixed with REACT_APP_ are embedded into the build
# and will be visible in the browser's JavaScript bundle. This means:
#
#   - These API keys can be viewed by anyone inspecting your application
#   - They are NOT truly secret in a React frontend application
#   - Malicious users could extract and misuse your API keys
#
# RECOMMENDED BEST PRACTICES:
#
#   1. Use API keys with appropriate rate limits and usage restrictions
#   2. Enable domain/referrer restrictions on your API keys when available
#   3. Monitor your API usage for unexpected spikes
#   4. For truly sensitive APIs, implement a backend proxy server:
#      - Client -> Your Backend Server -> External API
#      - This keeps your API keys on the server side only
#   5. Consider using serverless functions (Netlify Functions, Vercel API
#      Routes, AWS Lambda) as a lightweight backend proxy
#
# For more information on securing React applications:
# https://create-react-app.dev/docs/adding-custom-environment-variables/
#
# =============================================================================
